Tamarix chinensis

   [10276.jpg]
    Authority   Lour.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Violales:Tamaricaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names Chinese tamarisk, tamargueira chinesa
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 10276

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A deciduous shrub or small tree reaching up to 7 m in
   height and 15 cm in diameter, with a narrow crown of slender upright
   branches. USES It provides firewood and is planted as ornamental and
   hedges. The flowers are a source of honey. GROWING PERIOD Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES Tamarisk, Saltcedar, Palo de salitral, Tamarisco. FURTHER
   INF Scientific synonyms: T. ramosissima, T. pentandra, T. gallica.
   Tamarisk is native of southeastern Europe, central Asia, and China.
   Native habitat includes river banks, lake shores, marshes, humid
   alluvial plains, and steppes, often with salty soils. It has become a
   weed in southwesten United States spreading along streams, reservoirs,
   and irrigation ditches consuming large amounts of water.

   Sources
   SOURCES (T. chinensis Lour.)
   Shing T 1992 pp 325 [KTMP, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, SAL]
   Little E 1983 pp 268-270 [LIMIT, KTMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, PH, SAL]

